Currently Crowd generates XHTML 1.0 Strict:

{code}
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
{code}

We should move to HTML 4 Strict so that Crowd is in line with other Atlassian products for plugin/integration.

If a user deletes the last directory associated with their Crowd Console, they won't be able to log back in.

A workaround is if they have at least one remaining directory left, they can associate that directory with the Crowd Console application with some SQL.

Determine application ID for Crowd Console (32770 usually): 
{CODE}
SELECT * FROM APPLICATION
{CODE}

Determine an available directory:
{CODE}
SELECT * FROM DIRECTORY
{CODE}

{CODE}
INSERT INTO APPLICATIONDIRECTORIES (APPLICATIONID, DIRECTORYID, ALLOWALLTOAUTHENTICATE) VALUES
  ('APPID','DIRID',true)
{CODE}

Most of the searches in the "Xxx Browser" screens of the Admin Console are now case-insensitive. But the following are still case sensitive. Please would you verify whether this is the correct behaviour.

* Session Browser for Application Sessions --- case sensitive on app name
{{/crowd/console/secure/session/browseapplicationsessions.action}}

* Session Browser for User Sessions --- case sensitive on user name
{{/crowd/console/secure/session/browseusersessions.action}}
But note that the User Browser itself is case-insensitive.

* Application Browser --- case sensitive on app name
{{/crowd/console/secure/application/browse.action}}

* Directory Browser --- case sensitive on directory name
{{/crowd/console/secure/directory/browse.action}}

Please add a new line in the {{help-paths.properties}} file, to link the new "Options" tab in the application viewer to the following document:
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CROWD/Enforcing+Lower-Case+Usernames%2C+Groups+and+Roles+for+an+Application

So the entry should look something like this:
{code}
help.application.view.xxxx    Enforcing+Lower-Case+Usernames%2C+Groups+and+Roles+for+an+Application
{code}
